==Legacy==
In February 1992, a remake of {{nihongo|''Planetfall''|プラネットフォール|Puranettofōru}} was developed and published by Japanese software development company [[SystemSoft Alpha|SystemSoft]] for the [[PC-9800 series|NEC PC-9801]], over eight-and-a-half years after the original ''Planetfall''.<ref name="PC9801 Library">{{cite web | url=http://pc98library.tistory.com/1571 | title=PC-98x1 게임 도서관 :: System Soft의 게임 목록 (1992년) | date=16 June 2011 | trans-title=PC-98x1 Game Library :: SystemSoft's Game List (1992) | publisher=PC-98 Library | language=ko | access-date=2 January 2017}}</ref>  There are differences in this enhanced remake: the game recognizes verb commands typed in [[kana]] (Japanese syllable system) or Latin alphabet. For convenience, some of the most common verb commands (Look, Take, etc.) can be accessed by pressing a corresponding button, but the player still has to type the name of an object. This remake also helps the player to interact with the environment by displaying a list of objects after the player has typed a command.  Also, unlike the original, the remake contains enhanced graphics; every location has a unique background picture, on which the text is super-imposed, like in the PC-9801 version of ''[[Zork|Zork I]]'' and ''[[Enchanter (video game)|Enchanter]]''.<ref name="PC9801 Library"/><ref name="PC98Zork">{{cite web | url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/pc98/zork-the-great-underground-empire/screenshots | title=Zork: The Great Underground Empire (1991) screenshots | publisher=[[MobyGames]] | access-date=2 January 2017}}</ref><ref name="PC98Enchanter">{{cite web | url=http://www.mobygames.com/game/pc98/enchanter-wakaki-madshi-no-shiren | title=Enchanter: Wakaki Madōshi no Shiren | publisher=MobyGames | access-date=2 January 2017}}</ref>

